*create a mailchimp api key and audience id
*install zod and mailchimp dependencies

- gather information from the ui
1. set input form and states to handled the onChange events in the browser realtime
2. set the state of the form to be updated in the state of the component
3. use the state to update the component
4. organize the data as it should be sent per mailchimp requisits and pre-made setup fields 
- validate the information from the user using zod library
- once validated pass the data object into a server component
- server component will validate data on server side establish a connection to mailchimp server
- send the data to mailchimp server to create a new subscriber
- and get a response successful or failure / debugging
